# Composable File Organization

Split Composable UI code into separate files by logical concern. Do not put an entire screen, its sub-components, and detail views into a single file.

## Rules

- **Screen file** (`*Screen.kt`): Only the top-level screen composable that wires ViewModel state to child components. No `private` child composables here — extract them into separate files.
- **Sub-components**: Extract each logical UI section (search bar, result list, detail view, card, filter row, empty state, error state, etc.) into its own file. Avoid grab-bag files that group unrelated composables.
- **Shared components**: If two or more screens use an identical composable (differing only by a parameter like placeholder text), extract it into a shared file rather than duplicating.
- **Public by default**: When extracting composables from a screen file, make them `public` (not `private`) so previews can be added naturally and the composable can be reused.

## Previews (MANDATORY)

Every public composable that accepts plain data parameters (not ViewModels) **MUST** have `@Preview` composables. This is not optional — do not skip previews when creating or modifying composables.

- Add **light + dark** previews at minimum.
- Place previews in the same file as the composable they preview.
- Keep preview/sample data in a dedicated `PreviewData.kt` file per feature package.
- When creating a new feature package, always create the `PreviewData.kt` alongside the composable files.

## File naming conventions

| Concern | File name |
|---------|-----------|
| Screen orchestration | `AnimeSearchScreen.kt` |
| Search result list/item | `AnimeSearchResults.kt` |
| Detail/info content | `AnimeDetailContent.kt` |
| Shared search bar | `MalSearchBar.kt` |
| State & models | `AnimeSearchState.kt` |
| ViewModel | `AnimeSearchViewModel.kt` |
| List with pagination | `ReviewsList.kt` |
| Card component | `ReviewCard.kt` |
| Filter button | `UpcomingFilterButton.kt` |

```kotlin
// BAD - everything in one file
// AnimeSearchScreen.kt (400+ lines with SearchBar, ResultItem, DetailContent, previews)

// BAD - grab-bag of unrelated components
// CardComponents.kt (StatsRow, SearchBar, FilterButton, EmptyItem all in one file)

// GOOD - split by concern
// AnimeSearchScreen.kt   → screen + ViewModel wiring only
// AnimeSearchResults.kt  → result list + item composable + previews
// AnimeDetailContent.kt  → detail view composable + previews
// MalSearchBar.kt        → shared search bar + previews
// ListSearchBar.kt       → list filter search bar + previews
// FilteredEmptyItem.kt   → empty state for filtered lists + previews
```
